The text of 77—8 is according to the best MS. authority.

86. sectari. Note the frequentative, ‘ dance attendance on her.' The word was used of the young men who frequented the society of the famous philosophers and sophists.

in ludum ducere, ‘to escort her to her school,' i.e. where she had music lessons, her value as a slave depending on her aecomplishments.

redducere. The double d is confirmed by Lucretius. who lengthens the first syllable, and it appears as a correction in D and Andr. 559 in A.
